    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process introduced by the Eastman Kodak Co. in the early 1930s for printing color images from gelatin matrices which are prepared by exposure to separation negatives. The process is seen as a prototype for the modern-day dye transfer process.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000020881/International Center of Photography Encyclopedia of Photography (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>伊士曼‧柯達公司(Eastman Kodak Co.)於1930年代開發，由透過分色負片曝光的明膠印模，印製出彩色圖像的印刷術。此技術被視為現代染料轉印法的原型。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
